The paper discusses the use of physiological signals for continuous authentication, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The study also involves the use of wearable devices, specifically smartbands, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also mentions the use of these devices in smart home applications and IoT devices, which can be classified under cyber-physical systems (cs.CY). The study involves the use of machine learning algorithms, which can be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of working with physiological signals from wearable devices, which can be classified under signal processing (cs.SI).
